							"text": "Risk reduction and elimination is a core accountability and a key outcome from our systems approach to quality. Risks include those whose consequences are \"unacceptable\" and must be eliminated; and those which are \"residual\" and arise from the normal course of business. The elimination of \"unacceptable risks\" usually entails changes to operations and to physical resources. The management of \"residual risks\" usually involves procedural control, training and review.",
